            },
            "answer_text": "A more cynical (realistic?) version of Tyler's answer. The entire thing is a big stage show.  Bands come on for encores and even plays don't fully end when the curtain goes down. The politically committed get to root for their team a little longer and become more entrenched. The undecided can be further swayed by charisma and non-verbal behaviors.  Fine characteristics to unwittingly select a president on btw. Most everyone loses in some way except the network who always wins the longer you tune in. Which brings us back to your why question. ",
